==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metonymy
<hw>Me*ton"y*my</hw> <pr>(m⟦esl⟧*t⟦ocr⟧n"⟦icr⟧*m⟦ycr⟧; 277)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>metonymia</ets>, Gr. <grk>metwnymi`a</grk>;
<grk>meta`</grk>, indicating change + <grk>'o`nyma</grk> , for
<grk>'o`noma</grk> a name: cf. F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧tonymie</ets>. See
<er>Name</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A trope in which one word
is put for another that suggests it; <as>as, we say, a man keeps a good
<examp>table</examp> instead of good <ex>provisions</ex>; we read
<examp>Virgil</examp>, that is, his <ex>poems</ex>; a man has a warm
<examp>heart</examp>, that is, warm <ex>affections</ex>; a city dweller
has no <examp>wheels</examp>, that is, no automobile.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metope</ent>⟦br⟧
